Police made arrests during a public auction at the Agricultural Fund building in Pilsen
The anti-corruption police made several arrests at the Agricultural Fund building in recent days.
Detectives handcuffed a local media businessman and real estate businessman Luboš G.
Apparently, the latter attempted to manipulate an ongoing public auction for the restitution of rights in such a way that the auctioned land would be received by a specific interested party.
He had to pay Luboš G. half a million crowns for it.
&quot;At the moment I can only say that the police are looking for a person for bribery during a public auction and public tender,&quot; Pilsen Attorney General Antonie Zelená told Právo, adding that at the moment she cannot disclose more details about ongoing investigation.
After 24 hours, the police released the 46-year-old businessman.
On the way in which he was able to influence the public auction, given the little official information, one can only speculate.
The Lubomíra Agricultural Fund spokesperson Černá responded to Právo&#39;s questions saying that the police actually carried out the arrest at the Pilsen headquarters and it was during a public auction.
&quot;This is a client, not one of our workers,&quot; he said.
According to Černá, the public auction is called &quot;Call for the presentation of proposals for transfer of land in accordance with the law on land&quot; and is carried out when several interested parties appear in relation to the offered land.
&quot;These people, during the summons, offer a higher value than their restitution, which must be transferred before the value of the land is announced.&quot;
&quot;Based on the offers, the order of the buyers is determined and, later, the Agricultural Fund transfers the land to the person who offers the highest offer,&quot; explained the Fund&#39;s spokeswoman.
Luboš G. had information on who was going to present to the call and, given that he is also an interested person because he acquired various restitution rights, he proposed to those interested in the land that he would not participate in the auction.
