&quot;I was really fascinated by the fact that they wanted a place at the 2012 Nuclear Security Summit.&quot;
&quot;This shows that this process is working,&quot; said Ken Luongo, president of the Society for Global Security, a group that promotes nuclear security.
Clinton said the agreement is &quot;a very significant and important step&quot; taken by Belarus.
In April 2009 Obama promised in Prague to protect all vulnerable nuclear material around the world for the next four years.
Since then, the US government has helped six countries get rid of all of their highly enriched uranium.
